The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation
		 Thursday, April 22, 2004 				 Eve-tease clash
																								Hardwar, April 21 (PTI): A person was killed when police opened fire on a mob protesting against alleged eve teasing by constables, prompting the authorities to clamp indefinite curfew in parts of the city today.																								Over 100 people were injured in the clash that erupted last night after a group of policemen allegedly misbehaved with the wife of a local trader.																								Members of the trading community set fire to a police post in the Kharkhari area and a police vehicle. The police opened fire, injuring two persons, principal secretary (home) S.K. Das and director-general of police P.D. Taturi said. The police also resorted to lathicharge and arson. 
